	<gb/>

	<pb facs="liv_000019_0741" n="0741"/><!-- Everyone, change and repeat as necessary. -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><add place="margintop" hand="#U" rend="gray right"><fw n="741">741</fw></add>
<lb/><note place="marginleft"><date when="1872-02-20">1872 <lb/><choice><abbr>Feby</abbr><expan>February</expan></choice> <lb/>20<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi></date></note>
<lb/>I am greatly more elated by the unexpected
<lb/>kindness of unknown friends, and the
<lb/>liberality and sympathy of <unclear>H M</unclear> Government
<lb/>than cast down by losses and obstacles
<lb/>But I have a purpose in view in mentioning
<lb/>mishaps - Before leaving <placeName><geogName type="island">Zanzibar</geogName></placeName> in 
<lb/><date when="1866">1866</date> I paid for and dispatched a stock of
<lb/>goods to be placed in depot at <placeName><settlement type="town">Ujiji</settlement></placeName>. In
<lb/><placeName><geogName>Banzamweze</geogName></placeName> <!--geog:--> posters or <term type="occupation">Pagazi</term> as usual
<lb/>brought them honestly to this <term type="occupation">governor</term> or <orgName>Banian</orgName>
<lb/>agent - The same who <unclear>plundered</unclear> <persName>Burton</persName> and
<lb/>spoke pretty freely and he placed my goods in
<lb/>charge of his own <orgName>slave</orgName> <persName>Musa bin Saloom</persName>
<lb/>who about and very between this &amp; <placeName><settlement type="town">Ujiji</settlement></placeName>
<lb/>stopped the caravan ten days while he plundered
<lb/>as much as he chose and went off to buy ivory
<lb/>for his owner in <placeName>Karagwe</placeName> <!--geog:--> - <persName>Saloom</persName> has been
<lb/>kept out of the way ever since - The dregs of tea
<lb/>stores left by this <orgName>slave</orgName> are the only supplies I
<lb/>have <choice><sic>recieved</sic><corr>received</corr></choice> since <date when="1866">1866</date> - Another stock of 
<lb/>goods was dispatched from <placeName><geogName type="island">Zanzibar</geogName></placeName> in <date when="1868">1868</date>
<lb/>but the whole was devoured at this place -
<lb/>and the letters destroyed so that I should know
<lb/>nothing about them - Another large supply
<lb/>sent through <persName>Ludha</persName> and his <orgName>slaves</orgName> in <date when="1869">1869</date>
<lb/>- It came to <placeName><settlement type="town">Ujiji</settlement></placeName> and except a few pounds <add place="above">of worthless <unclear>wages</unclear></add>
<lb/>out of 200 <choice><abbr>lbs</abbr><expan>pounds</expan></choice> of fine dear beads all were sold
<lb/>off for <orgName>slaves</orgName> and ivory by the person selected
<lb/>by <persName>Ludha Damji</persName> - I refer to these wholesale
<lb/>losses because though well known to <persName>Ludha</persName>
<lb/>and all the <orgName>Banians</orgName> the statement was made
<lb/>in the <placeName>House of Lords</placeName> <!--I am not sure how to tag this, but it sounds like a physical place - AK-->, I suppose on the strength
<lb/>of <persName>Ludha</persName>'s plausible fables that all my <unclear>lowly</unclear>
<lb/>round about route of 300 miles from <placeName><settlement type="town">Ujiji</settlement></placeName>
<lb/>I did find two days ago a good quantity of
<lb/>supplies the remains of what had been 
<lb/>sent off from <persName>Banzubar</persName> <date when="1870-10">sixteen months ago</date></p>
			    
	<pb facs="liv_000019_0742" n="0742"/><!-- Everyone, change and repeat as necessary. -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><add place="margintop" hand="#U" rend="gray left"><fw n="742">742</fw></add>
<lb/><note place="marginleft"><date when="1872-02-20">1872 <lb/><choice><abbr>Feby</abbr><expan>February</expan></choice> <lb/>20</date></note>
<lb/><persName>Ludha</persName> had again been employed and
<lb/>the <orgName>slaves</orgName> he selected began by loitering
<lb/>at <placeName><settlement type="town"><choice><sic>Bagamoio</sic><corr>Bagamoyo</corr></choice></settlement></placeName> opposite of <placeName><geogName type="island">Zanzibar</geogName></placeName> for
<lb/>nearly four months - A war here which is
<lb/>still going on gave them a good excuse for
<lb/>going no further. The <term type="occupation">headmen</term> were <term type="occupation">thieves</term>
<lb/>and had I not returned and seized what
<lb/>remained I should again have lost all
<lb/>all the <orgName>slaves</orgName> who have been sent by <persName>Ludha</persName>
<lb/>and other <orgName>Banians</orgName> were full of the idea
<lb/>that they were not a follow but force me
<lb/>back - I cannot say that I am altogether 
<lb/>free from chagrin in view of the worry
<lb/>thwarting, baffling which the <orgName>Banian</orgName>
<lb/>and their <orgName>slaves</orgName> have inflicted - Common
<lb/><term type="occupation">Traders</term> <choice><sic>recieve</sic><corr>receive</corr></choice> supplies of merchandise
<lb/>from the coast and send loads of ivory
<lb/>down by the same <term type="occupation">pagazi</term> or <term type="occupation">carriers</term> we
<lb/>employ without any loss <unclear>Bent</unclear> the <orgName><choice><sic>Bainans</sic><corr>Banians</corr></choice></orgName>
<lb/><add place="above">and my <term type="occupation">agents</term></add> <add place="below">^</add> are not <hi rend="underline">their</hi> enemies - I have lost more
<lb/>than two years in time - have been burdened
<lb/>with 1800 miles of tramping and how
<lb/>much waste of money I cannot say -
<lb/>through my affairs having been <unclear>completed</unclear>
<lb/>to <orgName>Banians</orgName> and their <orgName>slaves</orgName> who are
<lb/>not men - I have adhered in spite of 
<lb/>losses with a sort of <persName>John Bullish</persName>
<lb/>tenacity to my task and while bearing
<lb/>misfortune in as manly a way as
<lb/>possible, it strikes me that it is
<lb/>well that I have been <choice><sic>brough</sic><corr>brought</corr></choice> face
<lb/>to face with the <orgName>Banian</orgName> system that
<lb/>inflicts enormous <unclear>envilson</unclear> <bloc>central
<lb/>Africa</bloc> - Gentlemen in <country>India</country> who
<lb/>see only the wealth brought to <persName>Bemba</persName>
<lb/>and Catch and know that the
<lb/>religion of the <orgName>Banians</orgName> does not
<lb/>allow them to harm a fly very <unclear>over</unclear></p>
			    
    <pb facs="liv_000019_0743" n="0743"/><!-- Everyone, change and repeat as necessary. -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><add place="margintop" hand="#U" rend="gray left"><fw n="743">743</fw></add>
<lb/><list><item><seg rend="right">pages</seg></item>
<lb/><item>Despatch to <persName>Lord Russell</persName> of <date when="1865-11-28">28 <choice><abbr>Nov</abbr><expan>November</expan></choice> 1865</date> N°1<seg rend="right">I II III</seg></item>
<lb/><item>Passage in "Thule" to <placeName><geogName type="island">Zanzibar</geogName></placeName> - <date when="1866-01-28">28 January 1866</date><seg rend="right">IV</seg></item>
<lb/><item>Deliver the "Thule" to the <term type="occupation">Sultan</term>. Visit <term type="occupation">Sultan</term><seg rend="right">V. VI</seg></item>
<lb/><item><persName><term type="occupation">Baron</term> van der Decker</persName> killed in the <placeName><geogName type="river">R. Juba</geogName></placeName><seg rend="right">VII</seg></item>
<lb/><item>Depositions of witnesses. <persName>Maya Mabrook</persName><seg rend="right">VIII</seg></item>
<lb/><item><persName>Hamada</persName> another <persName>Mabrook</persName> (<persName>Hajee Ali</persName> <term type="occupation">chief</term><seg rend="right">/ IX</seg></item>
<lb/><item><persName>Mabrook</persName> speak<seg rend="right">XV XI</seg></item>
<lb/><item><persName><term type="occupation">Baron</term></persName> killed by <persName>Somanlies</persName> at <placeName><settlement type="town">Barderatown</settlement></placeName><seg rend="right">XII</seg></item>
<lb/><item><persName>Sulieman</persName>'s deposition<seg rend="right">XIII</seg></item>
<lb/><item><persName>Muhamad bin Shamlan Hadramande</persName> &amp; <persName>Mobarek</persName><seg rend="right">XIV</seg></item>
<lb/><item><persName>Austrian offrer von Schiekt</persName> escapes<seg rend="right">page 2 of journal or XV</seg></item>
<lb/><item>The <persName><term type="occupation">Baron</term></persName> &amp; <persName>von Schiekh</persName>'s haughtiness<seg rend="right"><date><!--Not sure when this is referring to -AK--><hi rend="double-underline">January</hi></date> page 3</seg></item>
<lb/><item>Letter of the <term type="occupation">Baron</term> <date when="1865-07-30">30 July 1865</date> to <persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Seward</persName><seg rend="right">–</seg></item>
<lb/><item>Second letter to the <term type="occupation">Baron</term> to <persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Seward</persName><seg rend="right">–</seg></item>
<lb/><item>Third letter<seg rend="right">4 D.</seg></item>
<lb/><item>Coy of a letter from <persName>Sir Bartle Frere KCB</persName> to <term type="occupation">Sultan</term><seg rend="right">5 E.</seg></item>
<lb/><item>Visit of congratulation at conclusion of Ramadan<seg rend="right">5 E.</seg></item>
<lb/><item>Translation of <persName>Syed Majids</persName> reply to <term type="occupation">Governor</term><seg rend="right">–</seg></item>
<lb/><item><orgName>Slave</orgName> <persName>Dhow</persName> burned - <orgName>slave</orgName> market<seg rend="right">6 F.</seg></item>
<lb/><item>ancient coins with cufic inscriptions<seg rend="right">7 G.</seg></item>
<lb/><item>arrange with <persName>Koroje</persName> to send goods to <placeName><settlement type="town">Ujiji</settlement></placeName><seg rend="right">–</seg></item>
<lb/><item>Take leave of the <term type="occupation">Sultan</term> - his kindness<seg rend="right">–</seg></item>
<lb/><item>HMS. Penjin <persName>Lient Garforth</persName> - Embark men<seg rend="right">–</seg></item>
<lb/><item>and animals for <placeName><geogName type="river">Rovuma</geogName></placeName> - <persName>Dhow's</persName> draft too much<seg rend="right">8 A.</seg></item>
<lb/><item>Proceed to <placeName><geogName type="bay">Mikindany Bay</geogName></placeName> - Land at <placeName><geogName type="island">Pemba</geogName></placeName><seg rend="right">9 B.</seg></item>
<lb/><item>Real enjoyment in travelling<seg rend="right">–</seg></item>
<lb/><item><placeName><geogName type="island">Pemba Harbour</geogName></placeName> - syphilitic <orgName>Arabs</orgName> of the Coast<seg rend="right">10 C.</seg></item>
<lb/><item>"The higher criticism"<seg rend="right">11 D</seg></item>
<lb/><item>The Srkar-a Suaheli <orgName>Arab</orgName> nervous v. excitable<seg rend="right">14 G.</seg></item>
<lb/><item><placeName><settlement type="village">Nyangedi village</settlement></placeName> of <persName>Makonde</persName><seg rend="right">15 A.</seg></item>
<lb/><item><placeName><settlement type="village">Tandahara <choice><abbr>vil.</abbr><expan>village</expan></choice></settlement></placeName> Jungle dense - employ <persName>Makonde to</persName><seg rend="right">–</seg></item>
<lb/><item>clear a path - climbing plants &amp; trees<seg rend="right">–</seg></item>
<lb/><item>Meat eaters stand most fatigue<seg rend="right">16 B.</seg></item>
<lb/><item>"Hints to travellers" nonsense<seg rend="right">17 - C.</seg></item>
<lb/><item><persName>Monginko</persName>'s <term type="animal">goat</term> brings out the fact that<seg rend="right">–</seg></item>
<lb/><item><term type="tribe">Sepoys</term> &amp; <term type="tribe">Johannese</term> are of different sects of <orgName>Moslem - <persName>Bon Ali</persName> our guide</orgName><seg rend="right">18 D.</seg></item></list> <!--Looks like someone, not livingstone, has handwritten "2 leaves" with a handdrawn hand pointing somewhere on the page -AK--></p>
			    
	<pb facs="liv_000019_0744" n="0744"/><!-- Everyone, change and repeat as necessary. -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><add place="margintop" hand="#U" rend="gray right"><fw n="744">744</fw></add>
<lb/><list><item><seg rend="right"><hi rend="double-underline">January</hi></seg></item>
<lb/><item><term type="insect">Tsetse</term> bite animals a second time<seg rend="right">19.2</seg></item>
<lb/><item>valley <persName>Mehambwe</persName> - carrier steals a shirt</item>
<lb/><item>is followed by <persName>Bon Ali</persName> &amp; fined</item>
<lb/><item><persName>Mandare</persName> or <persName>Numbo</persName> root <persName>Narri</persName> <choice><abbr>vil.</abbr><expan>village</expan></choice><seg rend="right">20.7</seg></item>
<lb/><item><placeName><geogName type="lakelet">Lakelet Nangadi</geogName></placeName> in <bloc>Matambwe country</bloc><seg rend="right">–</seg></item>
<lb/><item><placeName><settlement type="village">Nachuchu <choice><abbr>vil</abbr><expan>village</expan></choice></settlement></placeName> on <placeName><geogName type="river">Rovuma</geogName></placeName> left bank<seg rend="right">21. G.</seg></item>
<lb/><item><term type="plant">Gum bopal tree</term>.<persName>Makonde</persName> knowledge<seg rend="right">–</seg></item>
<lb/><item><term type="animal">Buffaloes</term> &amp; <term type="animal">camels</term> abused by <term type="occupation">Sepoys</term></item>
<lb/><item><placeName><settlement type="village">Ntande village</settlement></placeName> stockade <seg rend="right">22 A</seg></item>
<lb/><item>People who made a murderous attack on
<lb/>the boats in <date when="1862">1862</date> hold aloof now</item>
<lb/><item>The <term type="tribe">Makoa</term> or <term type="tribe">Makoane</term> half moon mark 23°</item>
<lb/><item>Leave the flanking plateau of <placeName><geogName type="river">Rovuma</geogName></placeName><seg rend="right">–</seg></item>
<lb/><item>Geological structure changes v so does vegetation</item>
<lb/><item><term type="insect">Tsetse</term> again - <placeName><settlement type="village">Makonde villages</settlement></placeName> clear <seg type="right">24</seg></item>
<lb/><item><term type="occupation">Sepoys</term> remarkably filthy in habits. <seg rend="right">–</seg></item>
<lb/><item><placeName><settlement type="village">Liponde village</settlement></placeName> - make forced
<lb/>marches with <term type="tribe">Johannese</term> to buy food <seg rend="right">25</seg></item>
<lb/><item><orgName>Nassick</orgName> boy rebels - has always been
<lb/>trying to get others to run away - does
<lb/>not want to work</item>
<lb/><item>Want of food in a wide district</item>
<lb/><item>Pass <persName>Nyamatolole</persName> &amp; <persName>Matawatawa</persName> <seg rend="right">26</seg></item>
<lb/><item>An old acquaintance - <seg rend="right">27</seg></item>
<lb/><item>Cross <placeName><geogName type="river">Rovuma</geogName></placeName> - <placeName><geogName type="mountain">M<hi rend="sup underline">t</hi> Chihoka</geogName></placeName><seg rend="right">–</seg></item>
<lb/><item>Reach <placeName><settlement type="village">Matumera</settlement></placeName> on <placeName><geogName type="river">R. Loendi</geogName></placeName><seg rend="right">28</seg></item> 
<lb/><item>Paid <persName>Bon Ali</persName> - <term type="occupation">Sepoys</term> who were
<lb/>left for five days at <placeName><settlement type="village">Leponde</settlement></placeName>
<lb/>while we went on to collect food
<lb/>for them refused to come on
<lb/>and offered <persName>Bon Ali</persName> eight Rupees
<lb/>to take them back to the coast <seg rend="right">29</seg></item>
<lb/><item><persName>Hareildar</persName> says all I said in my
<lb/>note of their refusal to do duty is true <seg rend="right">30</seg></item>
<lb/><item>English <term type="insect">house flies</term> in <bloc>New Zealand</bloc>
<lb/><term type="animal">pigs</term> - <term type="animal">cow</term> <term type="animal">buffalo</term> died <seg rend="right">31.</seg></item></list></p>
		    
			    
			    
			    
			    
			    
			    
		
		
		
		
		
		
		
		
		
		
		
		
		
			    
			    
			    

